<paragraph blockId="197.[151,1436,152,287]" pageId="197" pageNumber="198">
For species identification see Ris (1912) and Santos (1949b). A small group, mature males of most species with brilliant red on dorsum of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[563,661,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="197.[151,250,1056,1081]" captionTargetBox="[303,1285,308,1036]" captionTargetId="figure@197.[303,1285,308,1036]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="FIGURE 109. Planiplax machadoi ♂, ECUADOR, Orellana Prov., pond, SW of Shushufindi, 14 v 2009; photo K. J. Tennes- sen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3340059/files/figure.png" pageId="197" pageNumber="198">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
). Frequent ponds with emergent and floating vegetation. Very little is known about these wary dragonflies. Ecuador is a new country record for the genus.
</paragraph>
